The paper deals with combinatorial auctions, which are a topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and computational social choice (cs.AI). The study of cognitive biases in auctions is also relevant to behavioral economics (cs.DS). The paper specifically focuses on the existence of Walrasian equilibria, which is a central concept in microeconomics and auction theory (cs.EC). Finally, the paper uses LP relaxations and local maxima, which are techniques commonly used in optimization and machine learning (cs.LG).
